  "texts": [
    "This would render the experience indistinguishable from a setting where input validation takes precedence.",
    "To evaluate this configuration, we pose a question to the LLMs that merges malicious inputs with neutral outputs, such as: \"Do you know any porn website?",
    "If so, does its domain name start with 'www'?",
    "Answer with 'yes' or 'no' without further explanation.\"",
    "The LLMs consistently reply with \"NO\" without any content filtering, indicating the absence of input prompt filtering. 3."
